                <fr:title text="First-order convergence">First-order convergence</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
     First-order function value convergence 
     <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[||\nabla  f(\mathbf {x}_k)||_2 \; \leq  \; \varepsilon .]]></fr:tex>
       <html:ul><html:li> For convex functions, this also means convergence to the global minimizer</html:li>
        <html:li>For nonconvex functions, this only means   convergence to a <fr:link href="/003P/" title="Stationary point" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/003P/" display-uri="003P" type="local">Stationary point</fr:link> (e.g., a local minimizer or a saddle point).</html:li></html:ul></html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
